Quote: I may mention, in proof of the permanent character of the gold-field, that Major Croker has had numerous applications for permission to erect puddling machines. .. I find that the applicants are for the most part old Bendigo puddlers, who, no doubt, remember well the extraordinary success that waited on the efforts of those who first established this method of extracting the gold from the soil in Victoria.
