Quote: The Greytown correspondent of the <i>Heathcote Advertiser</i> states that a miner in that town, named John Duvain, has come into the possession of GBP450,000. There are also two brothers, puddlers, of the same place, who have lately received the intelligence from America of a third brother having made provision for the annuity of GBP250 per annum for each of them for life.
